In[5]:
looms_by_gem = {}

base_path = "../../source_data"

gems = ["gem1", "gem2"]

for gem in gems:
    looms_by_gem[gem] = {}  # inner dict for sample  AnnData object

    for sample in samples:
        # Build loom path
        loom_file = os.path.join(
            base_path,
            gem,
            f"loom_{sample}",
            f"{sample}.loom"
        )

        # Load loom
        ad = scv.read(loom_file, cache=True)

        # Ensure unique var names
        ad.var_names_make_unique()

        # Add metadata
        ad.obs["gem"] = gem
        ad.obs["group"] = sample

        # Store AnnData object by sample name
        looms_by_gem[gem][sample] = ad

        print(f"Loaded {loom_file}")

In[6]:
concatenated_by_gem = {}   # gem  concatenated AnnData

for gem, sample_dict in looms_by_gem.items():
    # -------------------------------------------
    # Extract all AnnData objects from this GEM
    # -------------------------------------------
    loom_list = list(sample_dict.values())

    # -------------------------------------------
    # Concatenate samples if >1 sample exists
    # -------------------------------------------
    if len(loom_list) == 1:
        concat = loom_list[0]
    else:
        concat = loom_list[0].concatenate(
            *loom_list[1:],        # unpack additional samples
            join="outer",
            index_unique=None
        )

    print(f"Concatenated GEM {gem}: {len(loom_list)} samples  {concat.n_obs} cells")

    # -------------------------------------------
    # Rename barcodes to match adata conventions
    # and append gem name (e.g., -gem1)
    #
    # Original loom obs index looks like:
    #     sample:AAACCCAAGAAATGGG-1
    #
    # Final result:
    #     AAACCCAAGAAATGGG-1-gem1
    # -------------------------------------------

    raw_barcodes = concat.obs.index.tolist()

    # Take substring after ":"  "AAACCCAAGAAATGGG-1"
    barcodes = [bc.split(':')[1] for bc in raw_barcodes]

    # Ensure suffix "-1"
    barcodes = [bc[:-3] + "-1" for bc in barcodes]

    # Append gem name
    barcodes = [f"{bc}-{gem}" for bc in barcodes]

    # Assign back to AnnData index
    concat.obs.index = barcodes

    concat.obs["batch"] = 0

    # -------------------------------------------
    # Save to output dictionary
    # -------------------------------------------
    concatenated_by_gem[gem] = concat

Concatenated GEM gem1: 6 samples  10061 cells
Concatenated GEM gem2: 6 samples  10153 cells
In[7]:
# ----------------------------------------------------------
# Concatenate all GEM-level AnnData objects into one dataset
# Final object will be named: loom
# ----------------------------------------------------------

# Order GEMs deterministically
gem_names = list(concatenated_by_gem.keys())

# Extract AnnData objects for each GEM in order
gem_adata_list = [concatenated_by_gem[gem] for gem in gem_names]

# If only one GEM exists, no need to concatenate
if len(gem_adata_list) == 1:
    loom = gem_adata_list[0].copy()
else:
    # Global concatenation
    loom = gem_adata_list[0].concatenate(
        *gem_adata_list[1:],   # unpack additional GEMs
        join="outer",          # union of gene sets
        index_unique=None      # keep barcodes as-is (already unique)
    )

loom.obs["batch"] = 0

# ----------------------------------------------------------
# Diagnostic output
# ----------------------------------------------------------
print(loom)

print("Total cells:", loom.n_obs)
print("Total genes:", loom.n_vars)
print("GEMs present:", loom.obs["gem"].unique().tolist())

# Cleanup
del(samples, gems, base_path, looms_by_gem, concatenated_by_gem)
